.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 290, \"end\": 293, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.9380564232720082, \"rank\": 0.06599971544130594, \"text\": \"Jew\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"antisemitism\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 75}, {\"ngram\": \"a child\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 86}, {\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 127}, {\"ngram\": \"the controversial 'Feast\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 155}, {\"ngram\": \"Dionysus' tableau\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 176}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics opening ceremony\", \"from\": 193, \"to\": 222}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 226, \"to\": 232}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 245}, {\"ngram\": \"an LGBTQ+ icon\", \"from\": 249, \"to\": 263}, {\"ngram\": \"a proud Jew\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 290}, {\"ngram\": \"boot\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 298}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French DJ and lesbian activist Barbara Butch, 43, stood front and centre among a glamourous lineup of models, performers and drag queens in a segment of the opening ceremony that has been dubbed \\\"blasphemous\\\" for supposedly parodying Leonardo Davinci's Last Supper painting, according to Christian figures around the globe.\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9981254553360869, \"rank\": 0.0018761747711298097, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 318, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\", \"score\": 0.9942257172359459, \"rank\": 0.005805347175922244, \"text\": \"lesbian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\", \"dbped