 725, \"end\": 730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999991737035121, \"rank\": 8.2630276420041e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999998348817053, \"rank\": 1.6089978905826784e-07, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 790, \"end\": 799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8211192713859257, \"rank\": 0.2178498725360418, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 862, \"end\": 864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999597686276852, \"rank\": 2.3636775320969632e-05, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The response\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 645, \"to\": 660}, {\"ngram\": \"a mockery\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic painting\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"his 12 apostles\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"outrage\", \"from\": 763, \"to\": 770}, {\"ngram\": \"conservative politicians\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 842}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Catholic Church's conference of bishops denounced the performance for its \\\"mockery and derision of Christianity,\\\" posting an official English statement that said: \\\"We are thinking of all the Christians on every continent who have been hurt by the outrageousness and provocation of certain scenes.\\\"\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 1174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 870, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999995557118, \"rank\": 1.7820630106026086e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 976, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9948401528872222, \"rank\": 0.005186605079557295, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1068, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.7507830716172316, \"rank\": 0.31698629284221613, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"bishops\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"its \\\"mockery\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 959}, {\"ngram\": \"derision\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"an official English statement\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"every continent\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"the outrageousness\", \"from\": 1120, \"to\": 1138}, {\"ngram\": \"provocation\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"certain scenes\", \"from\": 1158, \"to\": 1172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US House Speaker Mike Johnson posted that the performance was \\\"insulting to Christian people around the world,\\\" and \\\"the war on our faith and traditional values knows no bounds today.\\\"\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}, {\"begin\": 1252, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8211192713859257, \"rank\": 0.2178498725360418, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the war\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1300}, {\"ngram\": \"our faith\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"traditional values\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1336}, {\"ngram\": \"no bounds\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1352}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers of the opening ceremony apologised for any offense caused, writing that the performance was intended to represent Dionysus, the Greek god of wine, and raise awareness \\\"of the absurdity of violence between human beings.\\\"\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1592, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1487, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0229391902814626e-22, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.8444458537731633, \"rank\": 0.1812584331912957, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1372}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1376, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"any offense\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1423}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch has complained of antisemitism and \\\"cyber-bullying\\\" after Christians called the performance blasphemous.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1658, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"score\": 0.7507830716172316, \"rank\": 0.31698629284221613, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1599}, {\"ngram\": \"antisemitism\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"cyber-bullying\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1691}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Audrey Msellati, her lawyer, said that she was facing threats of \\\"death, torture and rape\\\", as well as \\\"numerous antisemitic, homophobic, sexist and fatphobic insults\\\".\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1706, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"score\": 0.9981332796952113, \"rank\": 0.0018702114392910407, \"text\": \"Audrey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Audrey_Roberts\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her lawyer\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1733}, {\"ngram\": \"threats\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1767}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"death\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1777}, {\"ngram\": \"torture\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"rape\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1795}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"numerous antisemitic, homophobic, sexist and fatphobic insults\", \"from\": 1809, \"to\": 1872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch \\\"intends to prosecute anyone who, in the future, seeks to intimidate her\\\", added Msellati.\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 1910}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1929}, {\"ngram\": \"Msellati\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Butch, a self-described \\\"love activist\\\" who grew up in a traditional Jewish household, her aim was to \\\"unite people, gather people and share love through music.\\\"\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2056, \"end\": 2062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.5496741015667194, \"rank\": 0.8192568918223465, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 1992}, {\"ngram\": \"a self-described \\\"love activist\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"her aim\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2102}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2111, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2132}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 2141, \"to\": 2146}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch told Attitude magazine in 2023 that members of her family were killed in the Holocaust, and she experienced antisemitism during childhood.\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attitude_(magazine)\", \"score\": 0.9999999136425723, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Attitude magazine\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attitude_(magazine)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attitude_(magazine)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"members\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"her family\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2213}, {\"ngram\": \"the Holocaust\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2242}, {\"ngram\": \"antisemitism\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2276}, {\"ngram\": \"childhood\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She found acceptance in the French Jewish Scouts, which she describes as a \\\"safe space\\\" with \\\"poor and rich kids\\\" where she learned to play the guitar and began to explore her sexuality.\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2323, \"end\": 2336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_Jews_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Jewish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_Jews_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_the_Jews_in_France\"}], \"noun_phra